icon.name: Economic relationships
icon.description: The capacity to exercise influence and leverage through economic interdependencies
icon.long_description: The capacity to exercise influence and leverage through economic interdependencies; measured in terms of trade relations, investment ties and economic diplomacy.

children.name: Regional trade relations
children.description: Ability to influence other countries through bilateral trade flows and relative dependencies
children.long_description: The ability to influence other countries through bilateral trade flows and relative dependencies. This sub-measure focuses on an economyâs relative importance as an importer, exporter and primary trade partner for other countries, based on annual bilateral trade flows.

children.name: Regional investment ties
children.description: Ability to influence other countries through foreign direct investment flows and relative dependencies
children.long_description: The ability to influence other countries through foreign direct investment flows and relative dependencies. This sub-measure focuses on an economyâs relative importance as a source and destination of foreign investment for other countries, based on ten-year cumulative flows of foreign capital investment.

children.name: Economic diplomacy
children.description: The use of economic instruments to pursue collaborative interests and beneficial geopolitical outcomes
children.long_description: The use of economic instruments to pursue collaborative interests and beneficial geopolitical outcomes. This sub-measure tracks economic diplomacy through free trade agreements and outward foreign assistance flows.

icon.name: Cultural influence
icon.description: Ability to shape international public opinion through cultural appeal and interaction
icon.long_description: The ability to shape international public opinion through cultural appeal and interaction; measured in terms of cultural projection, information flows and people exchanges.

children.name: Cultural projection
children.description: Cultural influences and exports that help to enhance a countryâs reputation abroad
children.long_description: Cultural influences and exports that help to enhance a countryâs reputation abroad. This sub-measure looks at online search trends in the region, exports of cultural services, global brands, and the international status of a countryâs passports, cities and heritage sites.

children.name: Information flows
children.description: The regional appeal of a countryâs media outlets and universities
children.long_description: The regional appeal of a countryâs media outlets and universities. This sub-measure looks at the online search trends in the region for selected national news agencies, newspapers, television and radio broadcasters, as well as the number of inbound international students from the region enrolled in tertiary education.

children.name: People exchanges
children.description: The depth and influence of a countryâs people-to-people links in the region
children.long_description: The depth and influence of a countryâs people-to-people links in the region. This sub-measure tracks the size of regional diasporas, and the attractiveness of countries as travel and emigration destinations.

icon.name: Defence networks
icon.description: Defence partnerships that act as force multipliers of military capability
icon.long_description: Defence partnerships that act as force multipliers of autonomous military capability; measured through assessments of alliances, regional defence diplomacy and arms transfers.

children.name: Regional alliance network
children.description: Number, depth and combined strength of defence alliances in the region
children.long_description: Number, depth and combined strength of defence alliances in the region. This is measured in terms of codified security guarantees, military personnel deployed in Index countries, joint military training exercises, arms procurements from allied partners and combined operation years with allies.

children.name: Regional defence diplomacy
children.description: Diversity and depth of defence diplomacy in the region
children.long_description: Diversity and depth of defence diplomacy in the region. This sub-measure assesses defence dialogues, defence consultation pacts, foreign deployments between non-allied defence partners, joint military training exercises, combined operation years and arms procurements from non-allied countries.

children.name: Global defence partnerships
children.description: Arms trade patterns indicative of global security partnerships and collaboration across defence industries
children.long_description: Arms trade patterns indicative of global security partnerships and collaboration across defence industries, measured in terms of annual arms trade flows and number of arms export recipients over a five-year period.

icon.name: Diplomatic influence
icon.description: The extent and standing of a stateâs foreign relations
icon.long_description: The extent and standing of a stateâs or territoryâs foreign relations; measured in terms of diplomatic networks, involvement in multilateral institutions and clubs, and overall foreign policy and strategic ambition.

children.name: Diplomatic network
children.description: The regional and global reach of a stateâs or territoryâs diplomatic offices
children.long_description: The regional and global reach of a countryâs diplomatic offices, measured in terms of total number of embassies, high commissions, permanent missions and other representative offices.

children.name: Multilateral power
children.description: A stateâs or territoryâs participation and influence in multilateral forums and organisations
children.long_description: A countryâs participation and diplomatic clout in multilateral fora. This sub-measure examines membership in select summits, diplomatic clubs and intergovernmental organisations, as well as financial contributions to the United Nations and development banks, and voting alignment with other countries in UN resolutions.

children.name: Foreign policy
children.description: The ability of government leaders and foreign policy bureaucracies to advance their stateâs or territoryâs diplomatic interests
children.long_description: The ability of government leaders and foreign policy bureaucracies to advance their countryâs diplomatic interests. This sub-measure aggregates qualitative expert-based judgements of how effectively leaders pursue their countryâs diplomatic interests, their demonstrated level of strategic ambition, and the wider efficacy of a countryâs foreign policy bureaucracy. This year, the sub-measure includes a one-time indicator measuring expert perceptions of the handling of the COVID-19 pandemic and its reputational impact on countries.
